805
00:43:24,567 --> 00:43:27,468
  promoters had little trouble  
      filling concert halls     

806
00:43:27,537 --> 00:43:30,137
   and ballrooms to capacity.   

807
00:43:30,206 --> 00:43:34,275
      White and black fans      
   clamored to see Fats live,   

808
00:43:34,344 --> 00:43:38,546
            sometimes           
     with explosive results.    

809
00:43:38,615 --> 00:43:40,915
   -COLEMAN: He had more riots  
         than any other         

810
00:43:40,984 --> 00:43:42,717
        rock 'n' roller,        
         uh, maybe ever.        

811
00:43:42,785 --> 00:43:45,720
     He had four major riots    
          at his shows,         

812
00:43:45,788 --> 00:43:47,288
  partly because of integration 

813
00:43:47,357 --> 00:43:51,692
   but also the fact that they  
   had alcohol at these shows.  

814
00:43:51,761 --> 00:43:56,030
   So they were mixing alcohol  
          plus dancing          

815
00:43:56,099 --> 00:43:58,633
     plus the races together    
       for the first time       

816
00:43:58,701 --> 00:44:00,234
    in a lot of these places.   

817
00:44:00,303 --> 00:44:01,936
       And it was leading       
       to a little fights       

818
00:44:02,005 --> 00:44:04,071
       which soon bloomed       
        into huge fights.       

819
00:44:04,140 --> 00:44:06,274
   And they called the police.  

820
00:44:06,342 --> 00:44:07,908
    -HARDESTY: We got caught    
          in two riots.         

821
00:44:07,977 --> 00:44:11,379
        And it wasn't --        
    it wasn't a racial thing.   

822
00:44:11,447 --> 00:44:13,414
       There was a fight.       

823
00:44:13,483 --> 00:44:15,549
  And with -- within the fight, 

824
00:44:15,618 --> 00:44:19,587
   the police decided to throw  
      tear gas in the hall.     

825
00:44:19,656 --> 00:44:21,856
      And everybody panic.      

826
00:44:21,924 --> 00:44:23,691
       Well, it turned out      
        not to be a riot,       

827
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:25,326
        but people tryin'       
          to escape --          

828
00:44:25,395 --> 00:44:28,663
     tryin' to get away from    
          the tear gas.         

829
00:44:28,731 --> 00:44:30,398
 When they started broadcastin' 
        that there was --       

830
00:44:30,466 --> 00:44:33,801
  where Fats Domino was playin' 
   and there was a race riot,   

831
00:44:33,870 --> 00:44:36,303
      that was a $1 million     
      exposure right there.     

832
00:44:36,372 --> 00:44:38,539
All the news media picked it up.

833
00:44:38,608 --> 00:44:40,474
     So that was publicity.     

834
00:44:40,543 --> 00:44:43,177
          But there...          
   It wasn't a real race riot.  

835
00:44:43,246 --> 00:44:45,413
